                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>From February 23 to March 6, 1948, Delegations from the United States, the United
                    Kingdom, and France, together with representatives from Belgium, the
                    Netherlands, and Luxembourg, met for the first part of the London Conference on
                    Germany. During the Conference, discussions took place between the American,
                    British, and French Delegations on certain aspects of the reparation question.
                    For documentation on this first part of the London Conference, including reports
                    and papers regarding the reparations discussions, see Chapter I, Part B.</p>
            </div>
